# PixelMint Website

A professional multi-page website showcasing PixelMint's mobile applications and services.

## 🎨 Design Theme

The website uses the **Matte Blue and Gold** theme consistent with the Reward Whiz app branding:
- Primary Blue: `#1e3a5f` (Matte Blue)
- Dark Blue: `#0f172a` (Background)
- Gold: `#d4af37`
- Gold Light: `#f4d03f`

## 📁 Project Structure

```
PixelMint/
├── index.html      # Home page with Hero, Apps, Process sections
├── blog.html       # Blog page with Monetag banner spaces
├── styles.css      # Custom styles and theme
├── script.js       # Interactive features and animations
└── README.md       # This file
```

## 🚀 Features

### Home Page (index.html)
- **Hero Section**: Eye-catching headline with call-to-action buttons
- **Our Apps Section**: 3 premium app cards showcasing:
  - Reward Whiz (your flagship app)
  - Placeholder for App 2
  - Placeholder for App 3
- **Process Section**: 3-step methodology (Design, Develop, Deploy)
- **Contact Section**: Simple call-to-action
- **Responsive Navigation**: Mobile-friendly menu

### Blog Page (blog.html)
- **Blog Grid**: Multiple blog post cards
- **Monetag Banner Spaces**: Three designated areas for SmartLink banners:
  - Top banner (after hero)
  - Middle banner (between posts)
  - Bottom banner (before newsletter)
- **Newsletter Signup**: Email subscription form
- **Blog List Items**: Additional articles in list format

## 🎯 Tech Stack

- **HTML5**: Semantic markup
- **CSS3**: Custom styles with CSS variables
- **Tailwind CSS**: CDN for rapid styling
- **Vanilla JavaScript**: No heavy frameworks for instant load times

## 📝 How to Use

### 1. Open the Website
Simply open `index.html` in your browser. No build process required!

### 2. Add Monetag SmartLink Banners

In `blog.html`, find the three banner spaces marked with:
```html
<div id="monetag-smartlink-banner-top">
    <!-- Replace this comment with your Monetag code -->
</div>
```

Replace the placeholder with your actual Monetag SmartLink code in these three locations:
- `#monetag-smartlink-banner-top`
- `#monetag-smartlink-banner-middle`
- `#monetag-smartlink-banner-bottom`

### 3. Customize Content

#### Update App Information
In `index.html`, find the "Our Apps" section and update the placeholder app cards:
```html
<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Your App Name</h3>
<p class="text-slate-300 mb-6">
    Your app description here
</p>
```

#### Add Real Blog Posts
In `blog.html`, update the blog post content:
```html
<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-3">Your Blog Title</h2>
<p class="text-slate-300 mb-4">Your blog excerpt...</p>
```

#### Update Contact Information
Change the email in the Contact section:
```html
<a href="mailto:your-email@pixelmint.app" class="btn-primary">
    Contact Us
</a>
```

### 4. Modify Colors

To adjust the color scheme, edit `styles.css`:
```css
:root {
    --matte-blue: #1e3a5f;
    --dark-blue: #0f172a;
    --gold: #d4af37;
    --gold-light: #f4d03f;
}
```

## 🎨 Customization Tips

### Adding More Apps
Copy an existing app card in `index.html` and paste it in the grid:
```html
<div class="app-card group">
    <!-- Card content -->
</div>
```

### Adding Blog Posts
Copy a blog card structure and add it to the grid in `blog.html`.

### Changing Icons
The website uses Heroicons via SVG. Replace the `<svg>` code with your own icons or use:
- [Heroicons](https://heroicons.com/)
- [Font Awesome](https://fontawesome.com/)
- Custom SVG icons

## 📱 Responsive Design

The website is fully responsive with breakpoints:
- Mobile: < 768px
- Tablet: 768px - 1024px
- Desktop: > 1024px

## ⚡ Performance

- **No Build Process**: Deploy directly
- **CDN Tailwind**: Fast global delivery
- **Minimal JavaScript**: Only essential interactions
- **Optimized Animations**: Hardware-accelerated CSS

## 🌐 Deployment

### Option 1: GitHub Pages
1. Push to GitHub repository
2. Go to Settings > Pages
3. Select main branch
4. Your site will be live at `username.github.io/repository-name`

### Option 2: Netlify
1. Drag and drop the folder to [Netlify](https://app.netlify.com/)
2. Instant deployment

### Option 3: Vercel
1. Push to GitHub
2. Import to [Vercel](https://vercel.com/)
3. Auto-deploy on commits

### Option 4: Traditional Hosting
Upload all files via FTP to your web host.

